git branches:
    git checkout "remote branch name": pull/create the remote branch locally
    (a branch in the remote repo with the same name need to exist, -b and/or git pull are not needed)

    delete branches:
    git push origin --delete "remote branch name": delete the remote branch
    git branch -d/D "remote branch name": delete the local branch (while not in that branch)

    git branch: lists local branches
    (-r: lists remote branches)

